        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b041",
          "text": "The cooperative movement was created in the Lancashire town of Rochdale in England in 1844 when a group of 28 weavers created a cooperative society to open their own shop. Within ten years there were over 1,000 cooperative societies in the United Kingdom.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "d977",
          "text": "Today, there are cooperatives in many domains of life — housing, enterprise, marketing, credit unions, agricultural production among others. The cooperative movement worldwide has and estimated one billion (1000 million) members and employs directly or indirectly over 250 million people.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "574a",
          "text": "The world’s 300 largest co-operatives have an estimated turnover of $2.2 trillion (International Cooperative Alliance, 2016). If your are interested you can download the International Cooperative Alliance’s Blueprint for a Co-operative Decade (2013) here.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 117,
              "href": "http://ica.coop/en/whats-co-op/history-co-operative-movement",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 83,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 254,
              "href": "http://ica.coop/sites/default/files/media_items/ICA%20Blueprint%20-%20Final%20-%20Feb%2013%20EN.pdf",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 250,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 242,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 207,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fa37",
          "text": "This short video (1:34mins) by the Cooperative Network offers a brief introduction to what a coop is and why it they create multiple benefits for communities and coop members.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8RCZPrUIU0o"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 16,
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8RCZPrUIU0o",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 11,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 54,
              "href": "http://www.cooperativenetwork.coop/",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 35,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e8fa",
          "text": "Given the importance of mutual self-help as a tool for building local economies that are able to gain some measure of autonomy from global corporations, it is perhaps unsurprising that many of the models described in this course have their roots in the cooperative movement. Credit unions, industrial and provident societies, mutual insurance societies, for example, are all Cooperative legal forms. Moreover, many of the small-scale local enterprises that are emerging, as described above, are choosing to become cooperatives. Let’s have a look at some inspiring examples.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2508",
          "text": "In the UK “there are nearly 7,000 independent co-operatives working across the economy. They contribute £37 billion to the British economy and are owned by 15 million people across the country.” — Cooperatives UK",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=90FL_bBE4mw"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "43e6",
          "text": "Here are some examples of very different cooperatives and networks of cooperatives that show the diversity of the growing cooperative movement around the world.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3d18",
          "text": "Mondragon",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 9,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "36c2",
          "text": "One of the world’s most successful cooperative experiments in the economic field is the Mondragon family of enterprises in the Basque Country of Spain. Founded in 1956, it grew from humble beginnings when a local priest started a small workshop making paraffin heaters to provide employment for graduates from an education project started in 1946. Today is the seventh largest Spanish company in terms of turnover and the leading business group in the Basque Country.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 413,
              "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asset_turnover",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 405,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
