          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1f08",
          "text": "Emilia Romana Cooperative Region",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 32,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e82b",
          "text": "Emilia Romagna is a small region near the Alps in Northern Italy which is economically very well off with high end car producers like Ferrari, Lamborghini, Maserati and Ducati all being based there. What is interesting is that Emilia Romagna decided to use the cooperative path as a strategy of regional development. The earliest cooperatives in this region are from the 1860s and by the 20th century they had established themselves in all sectors of the regional economy: consumer, producer, agriculture, housing, banking and insurance. The region counted on an impressive 3600 consumer coops and 2700 producer coops in the year 1921.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "24d9",
          "text": "This presentation (1hr 16mins) by John Restakis on the Emilia Romagna Cooperatives gives you an opportunity to take a deep dive into the fascinating history of this regional cooperative network.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": {
            "mediaResource": {
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bPpLaLcqz7E"
            }
          },
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 17,
              "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bPpLaLcqz7E",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 5,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IFRAME"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "768a",
          "text": "Today there are three major cooperative movements in this region: the Lega coop group has more than a million members and provides 40,000 jobs; the Confcoop unites 1,858 cooperatives with a total of 284,000 members; and the Associazione joins 470 coops and 75,000 members. Together cooperatives in Emilia Romagna turn over more than 20 billion Euros each year (more).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 365,
              "href": "http://www.grocer.coop/articles/italys-emilia-romagna",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 361,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7336",
          "text": "“[…] what is truly fascinating about Emilia-Romagna is that whilst being one of the most economically successful regions in Europe, it is also one of the most cooperative regions in the world. With a population of nearly 4.5 million, nearly 2 of every 3 citizens are members of a cooperative. Cooperatives represent around 30% of the region’s GDP, making it a fantastic example of a true cooperative economy.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
