        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_25",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4a86",
          "text": "Rather than a conventional cooperative business, the CIC understands itself as a “transitional initiative for social transformation from below, through self-management, self-organization and networking” (CIC, 2016).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "f5bfccac727_26",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5076",
          "text": "This Catalan grassroots movement is radically experimenting with social innovation and has set itself the aim to create an integral cooperative public system, co-creating a cooperativist form of welfare that aims to eventually outperform the welfare state. Here is a short video (2min) trailer of the documentary ‘What a Strange Way of Life’ which also includes examples from the CIC. Members of the CIC were involved in creating the new crypto-currency Fair Coin and the Fair Coop mentioned in module two. In 2015 the CIC and the P2P Foundation started to collaborate on social innovation projects (more).",
          "metadata": null,
